  <div class="page">
    <p>A blockchain nearly works</p>
    <p>Our earlier work used a blockchain  Cryptographically proven integrity  No central authorities</p>
    <p>Unfortunately it didnt scale well  Blockchains dont really go past a few tens of transactions per second  Especially if transactions are large (attestation objects)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="page">
    <p>Unequivocable Log Derived Map</p>
    <p>Horizontally scalable public ledger with cryptographic integrity proofs</p>
    <p>similar to Certificate Transparency or Key Transparency, except:</p>
    <p>Clients only rarely communicate with auditors  Auditing load scales with number of additions to storage, not size of storage</p>
    <p>We designed the Unequivocable Log Derived Map to provide similar guarantees to a blockchain, when only storing objects</p>
  </div>
